('proj-network-debugger', 'ph-internet', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Network Debugging Notes', 'Optional practice project: Use DevTools to inspect a real page request waterfall, DNS/TLS timing, headers, cookies, cache, and failed requests.', 'side', 3, 'beginner', '{"whatToBuild":"Use DevTools to inspect a real page request waterfall, DNS/TLS timing, headers, cookies, cache, and failed requests.","buildSteps":["Define the Network Debugging Notes scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: network path, DNS behavior.","Sketch the core screen, state changes, empty/loading/error states, and accessibility expectations.","Implement the main UI flow with realistic sample data or API integration.","Add validation, responsive behavior, and feedback for at least one failure or edge case.","Capture screenshots or a short walkthrough showing the intended user path.","Document how to run or review the Network Debugging Notes deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/frontend","nodeKey":"proj-network-debugger"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Frontend Project Work through a focused Network Debugging Notes artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a reviewable Network Debugging Notes interface or component flow with screenshots and interaction notes is available for review.","The Network Debugging Notes scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
